Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <heguli97> Cool upload file feature, does it support every kind of file or is it limited currently to text files for example?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> HushList protocol doesn't care what kind of file it is. SilentDragon will need to learn some stuff to render a text file versus an image versus opening an external program for an arbitrary file, stuff like that

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> any arbitrary data, any file extension. Hush is about freedom of communication

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Supporting larger and larger files is more work, not just linearly, but new things need to be written to support files being larger than 1 memo or 1 transaction or 1 block, those are the big cut-offs. So those are the milestones of support

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Files that fit in 1 memo, 1 transaction, 1 block, and then I will assess if files larger than 1 block should be supported

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> These sizes work out to being about: 512 bytes, 200KB and 4MB

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> So first will come support for files up to 512 bytes, then files up to 200KB (both sizes will cost just one transaction fee by default, but miners could very well process these transactions slower if additional fees are not given). Files up to 4MB will incur multiple transaction fees, because they require multiple transactions to store. So a 4MB file will cost about 20X the fees as a 200KB file, because a 200KB file can be stored in 1 transaction, while a 4MB file requires many more transactions to store the data

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Miners are probably excited about File Upload feature, because it means the more people want to store files in Hush, the more transaction fees Hush miners will make. It creates a reason to make many Hush transactions, which makes Hush miners happy
